cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper discusses a new adaptive learning rate algorithm for stochastic gradient descent, which is a popular optimization technique used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed algorithm involves estimating the curvature of the loss function, which is related to numerical analysis, indicating that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with optimization techniques, which could also suggest that it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
